Bruegel: Triumph of Death. The torture stakes and gallows top right very close to the same motif top left in 'Hell Scene with Tortures' (based on 'Last Judgment') by a Bosch Follower, (panel, 62 x 56 cm, Sale Brussels, Palais des Beaux-Arts, 19-21 June, 1956. Nancy Dyke includes this picture in her 'Workshop A' (Bosch Imitators, c. 1515-1520), but this may be too early [= Nancy Dyke Corwin, The Fire Landscape: Its Sources and Its Development from Bosch Through Jan Brueghel I : with Special Emphasis on the Mid-Sixteenth Century Bosch "Revival", Ph.D. Thesis Univ. of Washington, Ann Arbor, 1980]. Look up Witt Library.
